    <briefdescription>
<para>Describes a single variable font axis. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A font variation axis consists of a four-character OpenType axis tag and a numeric value. Examples of axis tags include &quot;wght&quot;, &quot;wdth&quot;, &quot;slnt&quot;, and &quot;opsz&quot;.</para>
<para>This object is used to configure font variation settings explicitly. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
